Lumoin steps in with circular fintech for the building sector, enabling communities to manage materials, energy, and water sustainably. Through our verifiable data infrastructure, we ensure secure, compliant data flow, fostering actionable change and simplified financial reporting.

Harnessing the power of EU electronic wallets and a robust data infrastructure, we not only simplify financial reporting in the sector but drive actionable change by introducing novel capital and risk management models like Arup's layered buildings. This proactive stance steers the industry towards eco-friendly building practices, marking a departure from mere compliance to genuine transformation.

As global entities like the UN and UNECE refine trade document standards in harmony with EU digital wallet (eIDAS) principles, Lumoin is at the forefront, striving to realign international material flows in this resource-intensive sector. Our mission transcends the creation of a sustainable financial ecosystem; we envision a resilient, resource-efficient built environment, contributing wholesomely to both our planet's and our collective well-being. In Lumoin's stride, financial reporting follows the trail of actionable transformations, reflecting the evolved state of the building sector, not just its historical footprints.

description: DTS Plant Oy is a startup specializing in engineering software solutions for industrial plant design and optimization. Their flagship product is an all-in-one modular software that enables digital modeling of industrial plants, complete with integrated tools for process simulation, equipment sizing, hydraulic and mechanical calculations, and real-time project monitoring. The software aims to streamline engineering workflows, reduce project timelines, and enhance cost-effectiveness by providing accurate economic evaluations at every stage of a project. Designed with scalability in mind, the modular structure allows users to adopt individual software modules progressively without disrupting ongoing operations. Each module is tailored to specific project stages, combining technical engineering tools with economic modeling to ensure precision in design and cost estimation. DTS Plant Oy targets industries involved in large-scale industrial projects, such as manufacturing, energy, and infrastructure development. Key features include one-click tools for generating equipment sizes, weights, and material take-offs, as well as real-time process simulation for training and operational analysis. Their innovative approach leverages advanced algorithms and automation to simplify complex engineering tasks. The company's value proposition lies in its ability to increase efficiency, reduce costs, and provide high-accuracy estimations, making it a highly attractive solution for companies aiming to optimize their industrial plant projects. By focusing on modularity and ease of implementation, DTS Plant Oy differentiates itself from competitors, offering a flexible and user-friendly software solution.

description:

name: Sisusemi Ltd.
shortDescription:
Sisusemi solves the 2 major issues in the semiconductor chips: Advanced Nodes Yield and Chip Power Consumption.

As nodes shrink atomic-level surface defects become a critical bottleneck. SisuSemi add
description:
Sisusemi solves the 2 major issues in the semiconductor chips: Advanced Nodes Yield and Chip Power Consumption.

As nodes shrink atomic-level surface defects become a critical bottleneck. SisuSemi addresses this foundational issue, enabling faster adoption of advanced nodes with higher yield and reliability.

SisuSemi‚Äôs patented process restores surface integrity, enabling advanced node processing with fewer defects and better downstream compatibility. Our solution uses Ultra High Vacuum (UHV), elevated temperature (< 450 ¬∞C) and controlled oxidation to clean the silicon surface, restore the crystalline structure to the surface atoms and form a very thin crystalline SiO2 layer to protect the silicon surface and enhance further processing.

The technology is based on surface physics research made in University of Turku during the past 15 years. Sisusemi process is enabling technology of smaller components like ALD was 25 years ago.

name: UNITT - Universal Tokenized Technologies
shortDescription: UNITT is a chat-based payment system for selling creative content, monetizing responses by AI services, and rewarding users for receiving advertising.  UNITT works like an instant messaging app but al
description:
UNITT is a chat-based payment system for selling creative content, monetizing responses by AI services, and rewarding users for receiving advertising.  UNITT works like an instant messaging app but all interactions can be priced and sold from one user to another through tokenization. This means that content creators can sell their content on a pay-per-view basis, responses by AI services can be sold on a pay-per-reply basis, and brands can buy their customers' attention on a cost-per action basis.

We aim to create an ecosystem, where consumers can earn tokens by watching advertising and then use those tokens to purchase premium content and use paid AI chat-bots. 

UNITT's pay-per-view payment system enables content creators and AI companies to supplement their existing revenue streams with no cost of adoption. They can start earning incremental income from their first user in UNITT, and they can keep all their existing subscriptions and ad programs on other publishing platforms.

name: SGS Sensors
shortDescription: Some of the World's largest problems are invisible to the eye. Air pollution contributes to one in seven deaths. Every day, one factory experiences an explosion and dozens go through a costly producti
description:
Some of the World's largest problems are invisible to the eye. Air pollution contributes to one in seven deaths. Every day, one factory experiences an explosion and dozens go through a costly production halt because of a false alarm. Three billion tons of food are wasted, and 100 million cubic meters of methane are leaked to the atmosphere. Additionally, people spend time in meeting rooms and schools where the CO2 level can cause human cognition to be halved.

The common denominator is, that current gas sensors are not at the same time reliable and affordable. This leaves people and businesses unaware of critical data. The SGS sensors do not only bridge this gap, but go beyond with reduced power consumption that unlocks IoT use cases, flexibility for wearables and logistics, plus non-toxicity and easy recycling.

Little wonder then, that a dozen companies will pilot with us 2026, including one of the World's 50 largest. We could do plenty of name dropping, but we respect our NDAs.

description: The UltraPlex project develops a next-generation liposome-based drug delivery system for RNA therapeutics that is sustainable, cost-efficient, and scalable for pharmaceutical applications. Traditional liposomal formulations face challenges such as high production costs, solvent dependency, material waste, and therapeutic molecule encapsulation inefficiency issues, limiting their commercial viability. UltraPlex addresses these challenges by integrating green chemistry, nanotechnology, and focused ultrasound principles to create an eco-friendly and efficient drug delivery platform.

description:
Many construction materials have to be fire-retardant treated to pass the construction fire-safety regulations. However, many leading Fire-Retardant chemicals are currently categorized as Substances of Very High Concern in the EU, and possibly phased out in the near future. This regulatory disruption in the field will then open an exciting window for replacing and safe fire-retardant materials.

Our novel materials have indicated being not only safe, but also more effective in fire retardancy ‚Äì and no more costly than the traditional chemicals. 

In placing these very promising materials in the marketplace for the Fire-Retardant products manufacturers, our aim is to set up a Start-Up late 2026 as an Aalto University Spinout company. Aalto will transfer the technology and IPR to this Start-Up. We are welcoming investors to join this journey!

At Automata, we saw how i
description:
Today's AI coding tools fail because they expect a lot of wisdom with little order. Assumptions made by AI, or even humans, turn exponentially wrong as complexity increases.

At Automata, we saw how in nature, solutions to complex problems emerge from order, with just tiny bits of wisdom. So we started to build something totally different from existing software engineering paradigms. 

A system that doesn't assume wisdom from user or LLM turned out to work. For months, we've used Automata to develop even Automata itself, among other commercial projects. Today, 64% of specifications and 98% of code passes strict requirements without human intervention.

Sharpnav develops next-generation satellite PNT solutions designed for environments where traditional GNSS systems are unreliable. The company‚Äôs Low Earth Orbit (LEO)‚Äìbased technology delivers highly accurate and secure Positioning, Navigation and Timing  services that remain stable even under jamming, spoofing.

Originating from Northern Europe, Sharpnav focuses on delivering resilient navigation infrastructure for the Arctic region ‚Äî an area of growing strategic and economic importance as new sea routes. The same technology is now being expanded to serve broader European and Ukrainian needs, supporting defence, logistics, and critical infrastructure resilience in contested environments.

Sharpnav aims to deploy a global LEO-PNT constellation that complements existing GNSS systems and ensures reliable access to precision navigation anywhere on Earth. The company‚Äôs mission is to make PNT trustworthy, independent, and secure ‚Äî from the High North to every corner of the world.
